     <table 2 border="5pt" width="50%" align="left">
   <tr>
    <th> Mats Sundin </th>
    <th> Borje Salming </th>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td align="center"> Mats Sundin was born Feb 1971 and was drafted by the Quebec Nordiques in 1989 before being 
	traded to the Leafs in ‘94. He served 11 years as the team captain and made history by being the longest serving
	non-North American born captain. Mats recorded over 70 points every year for the Maple Leafs, and was the
	points leader for the Leafs the whole time. Mats Sundin is the Maple Leafs all time points leader and over his
	career, he has average over 1 point per game. Mats was inducted into the Hockey Hall of Fame in 2013, and was
	the second Swede introduced in the HHOF after Borje Salming. </td>
    <td align="center">Borje Salming: Borje Salming is a retired Swedish hockey player who played 17 seasons for  Toronto.
	Salming first played hockey for 6 years of his life in Sweden, before he was signed as a free agent by
	Toronto. In his rookie year, Salming recorded an impressive 39 points. Salming was selected for the First
	All-Star team twice and was selected for Team 2 six times. However, on November 26, 1986, Salming had the
	greatest setback of his life. While knocked down in front of the net, someone accidentally cut Salmings face
	with a skate blade. Salming required facial surgery and needed 200 stitches. Salming retired 5 years later
	and was inducted into the Hall of Fame in ‘96. </td>
   </tr>
  </table>
